                  </hi>I deal with the prosecutor. On the 16th of May, the prisoner came to me for 3<hi rend="italic">s.</hi>, which I paid him—I am sure he is the person—this is the receipt—he wrote his name on it "Runsford'—(<hi rend="italic">looking at it</hi>)—be brought a bag for some things which I had been cleaning.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence</hi>. I sent the other boy in, and be put his own name on the bill; be told me be was not paid, and he was to go for it on Mon<lb></lb> day morning—I did not go into the shop at all.</p>
